.SUBTITLE  ENABLE AUTOSCALE
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*ENABLE AUTOSCALE\*

.LM +8
.P 0;Selects the option to automatically scale and position an isometric or
perspective view on the graphics screen. 
.LM -8

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*FORMAT:        ENABLE AUTOSCALE

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Command parameters:\* _None
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*DESCRIPTION:\*
.p0; ENABLE AUTOSCALE ensures that any isometric or perspective view drawn on
a graphics screen, is correctly scaled and positioned on the screen.  
.BR; Using ENABLE AUTOSCALE a view is drawn so that it is positioned in the
centre of the screen, and extends almost to the edge of the screen in the
longer of the plot axes. 
.BR; If a quartered screen has been selected using the ENABLE DIVIDE command,
the view is positioned in the centre of the currently selected quadrant, and
scaled to fit the quadrant.
.p0; In order to determine the x and y plot coordinate ranges, two passes are
made through the data in the currently defined DTM area of interest.  
.BR; The first pass determines the coordinate ranges without output to the
screen, and sets up the plot scaling factor and origin.  The plot origin in
normalised device coordinates (ie. in the range 0.0 to 1.0) and the plot
scaling factor are displayed on the terminal. 
.br; The second pass, plots the isometric or perspective view on the
graphics screen.
.P 0;By default the scaling and positioning of the plot automatically by the
program is enabled.  The option may be deselected by means of the DISABLE
AUTOSCALE command; if this command is used, it is necessary to supply plot
origin and scaling values using the ORIGIN and SCALE commands. 
.p0; Use of the SHOW ENABLE command is recommended to check on the status
of the option before generating an isometric or perspective view.

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Messages:\*
.P0;The following error message is specific to the ENABLE command:
.LIT

*** ERROR *** Specifying command ENABLE
Command qualifiers are AUTOSCALE, BATHYMETRY, DIVIDE, FISHNET, GRAPHICS,
                       IFF_OUTPUT, OVERLAY, PRIMARY or SECONDARY

.END LIT

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Examples:\*

.P0;DTIVIEW>^*ENABLE AUTOSCALE<CR>\*
.br;DTIVIEW>
.!******************************************************************************
.PAGE
.SUBTITLE  ENABLE BATHYMETRY
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*ENABLE BATHYMETRY\*

.LM +8
.P 0;Selects the use of special display options for bathymetric data.

.LM -8

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.LIT
FORMAT:		 ENABLE BATHYMETRY
.END LIT 
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Command parameters:\* _None
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*DESCRIPTION:\*
.p0;The ENABLE BATHYMETRY command selects the program's special options for
displaying and generating a view using bathymetric data.  The option should
be enabled if the input DTM contains a large number of negative height
values defining the depth and shape of the sea surface.
.P0;When using this option, only nodes in the DTM that have negative heights
are modelled.  DTM nodes with positive heights are not modelled, so that the
land surface will always appear flat. Any vertical exaggeration value is
applied only to nodes with negative heights. 
.P0;Selection of the option also causes a special colour table UNDERSEA.DAT to
be read from the search list LSL$LOOKUP, so that when the view is drawn on a
screen, different depths appear in different shades of blue, and all land
appears in brown.  The display colours may be changed by editing the RGB values
in this file. 
.P0;The normal modelling and colour table options may be reselected by means
of the command DISABLE BATHYMETRY.  By default the bathymetry option is not
selected.
.p0; Use of the SHOW ENABLE command is recommended to check on the status
of the option before generating an isometric or perspective view.

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Messages:\*
.P0;The following messages are specific to the ENABLE and ENABLE
BATHYMETRY commands:
.LIT

*** ERROR *** Specifying command ENABLE
Command qualifiers are AUTOSCALE, BATHYMETRY, DIVIDE, FISHNET, GRAPHICS,
                       IFF_OUTPUT, OVERLAY, PRIMARY or SECONDARY

*** WARNING *** Current DTM does not contain any negative height

.END LIT

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Examples:\*

.P0;DTIVIEW>^*ENABLE BATHYMETRY<CR>\*
.br;DTIVIEW>
.!******************************************************************************
.PAGE
.SUBTITLE   ENABLE DIVIDE
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*ENABLE DIVIDE\*

.LM +8
.p 0;Selects the use of a quartered graphics screen.
.LM -8

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.LIT
FORMAT:		 ENABLE DIVIDE
.end lit
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Command parameters:\* _None
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*DESCRIPTION:\*

.p 0;ENABLE DIVIDE selects the use of quartered screen display mode. 
.p 0;If selected, the graphics screen is divided into 4 quadrants.  Each
quadrant is treated by the program as though it were a separate graphics
screen.  This allows 4 different isometric or perspective views to be
displayed and compared. 
.P0;The 4 quadrants are identified as follows:
.LIT

	1   =	Top lefthand quadrant

	2   =	Top righthand quadrant

	3   =   Bottom righthand quadrant

	4   =   Bottom lefthand quadrant

.END LIT
.p 0;On selection of a quartered screen, the default quadrant is the top 
lefthand quadrant.  A different quadrant may be selected using the QUADRANT
command.
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Messages:\*
.P0;The following message is specific to the ENABLE command:
.LIT

*** ERROR *** Specifying command ENABLE
Command qualifiers are AUTOSCALE, BATHYMETRY, DIVIDE, FISHNET, GRAPHICS,
                       IFF_OUTPUT, OVERLAY, PRIMARY or SECONDARY

.END LIT
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Examples:\*
             
.P0;DTIVIEW>^*ENABLE DIVIDE<CR>\*
.BR;DTIVIEW>
.!******************************************************************************
.PAGE
.SUBTITLE   ENABLE FISHNET
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*ENABLE FISHNET\*

.LM +8
.p 0;Enables the option of producing a 'fishnet' representation of a terrain
view.
.LM -8

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
.LIT
FORMAT:		 ENABLE FISHNET
.end lit
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Command parameters:\* _None
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*DESCRIPTION:\*

.P 0;ENABLE FISHNET enables the option of producing a 'fishnet' representation
of a terrain view when the ISOMETRIC or PERSPECTIVE command is given.
.P 0;A 'fishnet' representation involves drawing the 3-D terrain view as a
grid, rather than as a series of parallel profiles orientated along just one of
the DTM axes. Profiles are generated both vertically (south to north) and
horizontally (west to east) through the DTM. 
.p 0;A 'fishnet' representation enhances perception when dealing with a
sparse data grid (ie. when a small DTM window has been defined), but is
less successful when dealing with a dense grid. In the later case it can
lead to a poorer perception of the depth relationships in the model, by
making the incidental shading effects near the terrain horizons less apparent.
.P 0;In the current implementation of this option in DTIVIEW, true hidden
line removal is only applied to the first set of parallel profiles that
are generated. In the case of the second set of profiles that are drawn
to produce the grid representation, only partial hidden line removal is
performed to ensure that no vectors that are completely hidden by previous
profiles are shown. The actual intersection of the two sets of profiles
with each other is not carried out. The techniques that are used to overlay
vector data on a 3-D view are followed.
.P 0;By default the option to produce a 'fishnet' representation is not
enabled.
.P 0;Use of the SHOW ENABLE command is recommended to check on the status of
the option before a terrain view is generated.
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Messages:\*
.P0;The following message is specific to the ENABLE command:
.LIT

*** ERROR *** Specifying command ENABLE
Command qualifiers are AUTOSCALE, BATHYMETRY, DIVIDE, FISHNET, GRAPHICS,
                       IFF_OUTPUT, OVERLAY, PRIMARY or SECONDARY

.END LIT
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Examples:\*
             
.P0;DTIVIEW>^*ENABLE FISHNET <CR>\*
.BR;DTIVIEW>
.!******************************************************************************
