.SUBTITLE SPAWN command
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*SPAWN\*
.INDEX DTIVIEW> commands> SPAWN
.INDEX DTIVIEW> SPAWN command

.LEFT MARGIN +8
.P0; The SPAWN command enables a subprocess to be created from within DTIVIEW.
.LEFT MARGIN -8

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*FORMAT:                SPAWN command-line\*


.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Command parameters:\*

.LEFT MARGIN +8
.P-8;command-line
.P0; Specifies a DCL command string to be executed as if typed in response to
a '$' prompt. When the command completes, the subprocess terminates and control
is returned to DTIVIEW. The command line cannot exceed 80 characters. 
.LEFT MARGIN -8

.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*DESCRIPTION:\*
.P0; The SPAWN command enables you to create a subprocess while within
DTIVIEW. When the subprocess terminates, control is returned to DTIVIEW.
.P0
^*--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\*
.BR;^*Messages:\*
.P 0;The following error messages are specific to the SPAWN command:

